            "answer_text": "Well, the tubes in ENIAC burned out. ENIAC filled rooms. It weighed literal tons. It took 150000 watts to operate. Once, a literal moth got into the circuitry and shorted it out, and that became the basis for why we call errors in software \u2018bugs.\u2019 First generation computers aren\u2019t Apple //e. First generation computers solved the kinds of math problems in minutes that are less complicated than the unlock screen on your cell phone. ",
